#: ../iot/homeassistant/diy_device.rst:2
msgid "Add DIY Device with ESP32"
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/diy_device.rst:4
msgid ""
"You can add your purchased smart devices to Home Assistant, such as smart"
" sound, smart desk lamp, etc. You can also make your DIY device with "
"ESP32 and add it in."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/diy_device.rst:6
msgid "In this section, you will learn how to add your DIY device."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/diy_device.rst:8
msgid ""
"Before you start the following operations, you need to complete "
":ref:`Install and configure ESPHome`."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/diy_device.rst:10
msgid "**Add Integration**"
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/diy_device.rst:13
msgid ""
"Now, visit http://ip:8123 to access your Home Assistant, then click "
"**Configuration** in the left column and select **Intergrations**."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/diy_device.rst:18
msgid ""
"2. If Home Assistant finds a device on your network, it will display the "
"corresponding integration, which can be easily added with just a few "
"clicks. If your smart device is not yet discovered, don't worry, you can "
"add it via the **+ ADD INTERGATION** button at the bottom right."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/diy_device.rst:24
msgid ""
"Search for ESPHome in the pop-up window and fill in the Host (the IP "
"recorded after the INSTALL step in chapter:ref:`Install and configure "
"ESPHome`), with the option to place your esp-light in the bedroom, "
"kitchen or other area of your choice."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/diy_device.rst:29
msgid "After clicking Finish, you will see it in the list."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/diy_device.rst:34
msgid "**Edit Dashboard**"
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/diy_device.rst:36
msgid "Now a CARD needs to be added to control this esp-light."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/diy_device.rst:38
msgid ""
"Click **Overview** --> **Edit Dashboard** --> **ADD CARD**, you can "
"select the corresponding CARD according to your needs, for example, "
"select **Button** here, and then select the corresponding Entity."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/diy_device.rst:45
msgid ""
"After clicking SAVE, you will be able to use this Button to control the "
"esp-light (if you connect an LED to GPIO16 in ESP32 board, click on the "
"Button to make the LED light up or turn off)."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/diy_device.rst:50
msgid ""
"For more styles, you can refer to `Official Demo <https://demo.home-"
"assistant.io/#/lovelace/0>`_."
msgstr ""

